## Invocation

| Cue | Action |
|-----|--------|
| @planner "brainstorm" | Clarify, propose, approve → then write plan |
| @planner "write plan" | Bite-sized tasks, exact paths (dotfiles-plan) |
| @planner "execute plan" | One agent per task, then @code-reviewer |
| @planner "Task: [description]" | Full workflow: plan → implement → review |
| When handling a bug | Use dotfiles-debug (systematic-debugging command) |

## Anti-patterns

- **Skip plan** – No config/taskfile edits without a plan.
- **Skip review** – @code-reviewer is mandatory before commit.
- **Big-bang commits** – Prefer one logical change per commit.
- **Fix before root cause** – Use dotfiles-debug; no fixes before Phase 1 complete.

